<L>__{interior hotel rooms at the new people's hotel night}
<A>__{claire stryder, 40, reads a report over the telephone as she times the call with a stopwatch. a photograph of claire's high school aged daughter sits on her dresser. alex grazier, 50, struggles with his tie and a drink at a dresser in the adjoining room. their connected rooms are littered with hand washed laundry and the paraphernalia of their trade typewriters, tape decks, books, notes, pictures. their love affairs of three years is ending.}
